atford-on-Avon","Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894879/answer",,,,,"139347","2018-05-03T16:11:21.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894879/answer","Biography information for Nadhim Zahawi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894879/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-30","Pupils: Disadvantaged","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment he has made of the quality of educational support provided to 16 and 17-year-olds in need of help or protection.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","139348"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894880","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-05-03","<p>These statistics will be published in the autumn, in accordance with the relevant protocols in the Code of Practice for official statistics (dependent on user need and the quality of the associated data):</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.statisticsauthority.gov.uk/assessment/code-of-practice/index.html" target="_blank">http://www.statisticsauthority.gov.uk/assessment/code-of-practice/index.html</a></p><p> </p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894880/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T16:13:09.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894880/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894880/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-30","Work and Health Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 27 April 2018 to Question 137389, when she plans for the first performance data from the Work and Health Programme to be published.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","139349"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894881","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-09","<p>The cost of the Non-domestic Renewable Heat Incentive scheme was:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Financial year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2015/16</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2016/17</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2017/18</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Non-domestic payments</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£296</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£443m</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>£612m</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Note that the 2017/18 figure uses the latest available payment information and is correct up to end February 2018.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894881/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-09T11:46:24.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894881/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894881/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-30","Renewable Heat Incentive Scheme: Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what the cost of non-domestic renewable heat incentive subsidies was in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for John McNally","Falkirk","John McNally","139521"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894882","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-05-03","<p>A participant in the Work and Health Programme can be sanctioned if they fail to participate in the programme or fail to apply for a vacancy notified to them by their provider without good reason.</p>","Truro and Falmouth","Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894882/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T10:33:08.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894882/answer","Biography information for Sarah Newton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894882/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-30","Work and Health Programme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, in what circumstances a jobseeker participating in the Work and Health Programme can be made subject to a sanction.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","139350"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894883","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-09","<p>In 2016 (the latest year for which data are available), the UK energy demand for biomass was 8,542 thousand tonnes of oil equivalent (ktoe). Of this,</p><p>a) 46 per cent (3,935 ktoe) was domestically sourced wood, and;</p><p>b) 36 per cent (3,071 ktoe) was imported wood.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>2016</strong></p></td><td colspan="3"><p><strong>ktoe</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Wood<strong>[1]</strong></strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Other biomass</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Production</p></td><td><p>3,935</p></td><td><p>1,630</p></td><td><p>5,565</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Imports</p></td><td><p>3,071</p></td><td><p>41</p></td><td><p>3,112</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Exports</p></td><td><p>-135</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>-135</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Total supply</p></td><td><p>6,871</p></td><td><p>1,670</p></td><td><p>8,542</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4"><p><em><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/632546/DUKES_6.1-6.3.xls" target="_blank">Source: Digest of UK Energy Statistics (DUKES) 2017, table 6.1</a><strong>[2]</strong></em></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>[1] Wood includes waste wood, wood, and wood pellets</p><p>[2] An estimate has been made for the proportion of wood pellets included in the plant biomass category in DUKES</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894883/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-09T11:46:56.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894883/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894883/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-30","Biofuels","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what proportion of the total biomass used to produce energy in the last year came from (a) domestically sourced wood and (b) imported wood.","false","Biography information for John McNally","Falkirk","John McNally","139522"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894884","Department for International Trade","false","2018-05-03","<p>I refer the Hon Member to my previous answer of 23 April 2018, UIN <a href="https://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2018-04-23/137004/" target="_blank">137004</a>, which sets out that the details of these meetings are available on the Gov.uk website at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=department-for-international-trade&amp;publication_type=transparency-data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?departments%5B%5D=department-for-international-trade&amp;publication_type=transparency-data</a></p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894884/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T15:48:38.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894884/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894884/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-04-30","Legatum Institute","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, pursuant to the Answer of 26 April 2018 to Question 137004 on Legatum Institute,  between what the purpose was of the meetings between Antonia Romeo and the Legatum Institute between 16 October 2017 and 8 December 2017; whether (a) notes and (b) documentation pertaining to those meetings were (i) produced and (ii) circulated to (A) Ministers and (B) officials in her Department; and whether the Legatum Institute made any proposals on Department or Government policy at those meetings.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","139377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894885","Department for International Development","false","2018-05-03","<p>UK-funded partners including OCHA and other UN agencies are delivering assistance to those displaced from Afrin; this includes health, food, water, and nutrition and protection services. Both the UK and the UN are calling on all parties to facilitate access for life-saving humanitarian aid, and to allow freedom of movement for those caught up in the violence, in accordance with international humanitarian law.</p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894885/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T16:48:55.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894885/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894885/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2018-04-30","Syria: Internally Displaced People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she is taking with (a) the UN (b) the UN Office for the Coordination of Humanitarian Affairs and (c) other international partners to support displaced people in Afrin, Syria; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","139351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894886","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-05-03","<p>Research shows that many people come onto Universal Credit with pre-existing rent arrears. We also know that arrears are usually temporary and the majority of claimants do succeed in paying their rent, managing their monthly payments and clearing their arrears over time. In our research, the proportion of Universal Credit claimants who were in arrears at the start of their claim fell by a third after four months.</p><p> </p><p>We are currently carrying out further analysis of this issue with a number of housing providers, to investigate and understand the true level of rent arrears for their tenants, what is causing them and any impacts Universal Credit may be having. It will be published when completed.</p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894886/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T11:33:31.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894886/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894886/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-30","Universal Credit: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment her Department has made on the effect of the roll-out of universal credit on trends in the level of rent arrears in (a) the Enfield North constituency (b) the London Borough of Enfield and (c) London.","false","Biography information for Joan Ryan","Enfield North","Joan Ryan","139352"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894887","Ministry of Justice","true","2018-05-03","<p>I refer the honourable member to the answer to PQs 13<ins class="ministerial">7</ins>608-10, given on 27 April 2018.</p><p> </p><p>As we focus on making our jails safe and decent places to support rehabilitation between the end of October 2016 and the end of March 2018 we have increased prison officer numbers by 3,111, which is already significantly over our target of 2,500 additional staff by the end of December 2018. These recruitment efforts form part of a wider drive to ensure that all prisons are fully staffed so that they can deliver safe and decent regimes.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894887/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T15:40:33.013Z","2018-05-04T10:29:29.963Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894887/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894887/answer","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894887/answer/previousversion/55954","Biography information for Rory Stewart","54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-30","Prison Officers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether his Department has set a target for the net number of prison officers to be employed in the prison service in the next (a) 12 months and (b) three years.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","139558"
