"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894892","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-08","<p>The number of band 3-5 prison officers who took voluntary early departure and have since re-joined the Prison Service can be seen in the table below.</p><p> </p><p>The government has passed its target to recruit an additional 2,500 prison officers by the end of 2018 – seven months early. An additional 3,111 prison officers were in place at the end of March 2018 than were in post in October 2016. Continuing to boost staffing numbers is crucial as it will allow prisons to introduce a new model where prison officers spend more time both one-to-one and with small groups of prisoners.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Band 3-5 prison officers who took voluntary early departure and have since re-joined the Prison Service, 2010/11 to 2017/18 (1 April 2017-31 December 2017) </strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Headcount</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Restart date</p></td><td><p>Number of band 3-5 prison officers</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010/11</p></td><td><p>3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>~</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>106</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>40</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17</p></td><td><p>35</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1 April 2017-31 December 2017</p></td><td><p>14</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p>1. Voluntary exits can be offered where the organisation wishes to reduce staff numbers by offering an early exit scheme or an early exit package to an individual. There is no compulsion on individuals to accept the offer.</p><p>2. The time periods shown reflect the date of when the staff re-joined the Prison Service, and not when the voluntary early departure was taken.</p><p>3. Figures include 73 individuals that re-joined as a reserve.</p><p>~ denotes suppressed values of 2 or fewer or other values which would allow values of 2 or fewer to be derived by subtraction. Low numbers are suppressed to prevent disclosure in accordance with the Data Protection Act, 1998.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894892/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-08T15:10:18.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894892/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894892/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-30","Prison Officers: Re-employment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prison officers who took voluntary early departure have been re-recruited by HM Prison Service in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","139563"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894893","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-09","<p>The number of band 3-5 prison officers who have taken voluntary early departure since 2009/10 can be found in table 11b in the latest HMPPS Workforce Statistics publication:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/her-majestys-prison-and-probation-service-workforce-quarterly-december-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/her-majestys-prison-and-probation-service-workforce-quarterly-december-2017</a></p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894893/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-09T12:11:59.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894893/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894893/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-30","Prison Officers: Redundancy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prison officers have taken voluntary early departure in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","139564"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894894","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-08-17","<p>Due to the way in which the information is held by the pensions administrator, the average annual severance package for Band 3 to 5 officers taking Voluntary Exit or Voluntary Redundancy cannot be separately identified.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894894/answer",,,,,,"2018-08-17T09:24:46.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894894/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894894/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-30","Prison Officers: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the average severance package was for a prison officer taking voluntary early departure in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","139565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894895","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-04","<p>This level of information cannot be supplied due to the risk of identification of individuals. It is therefore exempt from disclosure under the Data Protection Act 1998 (DPA).</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894895/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-04T16:07:38.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894895/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894895/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-30","Prison Officers: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the severance package was for each prison officer who took voluntary early departure and was subsequently re-recruited by HM Prison and Probation Service in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","139566"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894896","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-05-10","<p>The information requested is not held centrally and could only be collated at disproportionate cost.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894896/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-10T16:39:35.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894896/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894896/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-04-30","Prison Officers: Redundancy Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the value was of severance packages for prison officers that took voluntary early departure and were subsequently re-recruited since after 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","139567"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894897","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-05-03","<p>The Government continues to work on the design and priorities of the UK Shared Prosperity Fund (UKSPF). We will consult with the Devolved Administrations in due course regarding how the UKSPF might work in their nations, recognising their expertise in delivering the structural funds.</p><p> </p>","Rossendale and Darwen","Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894897/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T12:55:35.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894897/answer","Biography information for Jake Berry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894897/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-04-30","EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what discussions he has had with the (a) the Secretary of State for Wales and (b) Welsh Government on the design and implementation of the UK Shared Prosperity Fund after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","139401"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894898","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-05-10","<p>We have assessed the environmental impacts of oxo-biodegradable plastics across their life cycle and, as a consequence, have no current plans to make the use of oxo-biodegradation additives mandatory in the manufacture of everyday plastic items.</p><p>The current evidence on the overall environment benefits of oxo-biodegradable plastic is not conclusive. The main concern which has been raised is that oxo-biodegradable plastics could take time to degrade without oxygen and sunlight once they have leaked into the broader environment. It is suggested that this lack of complete degradation could result in the generation of micro plastics, which can be more harmful to the environment and aquatic life. We will continue to look closely at, and be driven by, the evidence on this issue.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894898/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-10T14:34:01.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894898/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894898/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-30","Plastics: Biodegradability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what assessment his Department has made of the merits of making it obligatory for manufacturers to include oxo biodegradation additives in everyday plastic items.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","139578"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894899","Department for International Trade","false","2018-05-03","<p>No applications were received and no support was provided to these companies in the last five years.</p><p>Where such information is not commercially sensitive, UK Export Finance (UKEF) publishes details of the companies it has supported on an annual basis in its Annual Report and Accounts which are presented to Parliament and can be found on UKEF’s website.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/uk-export-finance-annual-reports-and-accounts" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/uk-export-finance-annual-reports-and-accounts</a></p>","Beverley and Holderness","Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894899/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T13:26:10.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894899/answer","Biography information for Graham Stuart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894899/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2018-04-30","UK Export Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many applications UK Export Finance has received from (a) Leonardo, (b) Agusta Westland and (c) Selex in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","139591"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894900","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-05-04","<p>We do not have any recent estimates of the number of animal rescue homes in England.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894900/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-04T14:08:43.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894900/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894900/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-30","Animal Welfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what estimate he has made of the number of animal rescue homes in England.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","139607"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894901","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2018-05-03","<p>According to the website of the Association of Dogs and Cats Homes there are 76 full members and 55 associate members.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894901/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T10:31:47.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894901/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894901/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2018-04-30","Animal Welfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 27 April to Question 904960 on Animal Welfare, how many animal rescue homes are members of the Association of Dogs and Cats Homes.","false","Biography information for Jo Platt","Leigh","Jo Platt","139608"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894902","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-09","<p>This Government is committed to improving perinatal mental health services for women during pregnancy and in the first postnatal year, so that women are able to access the right care at the right time and close to home.</p><p> </p><p>The Department is investing £365 million to 2020/21 in perinatal mental health services, and NHS England is leading a transformation programme with the development of specialist perinatal mental health community services across England with their investment of £63 million between 2016/17 and 2018/19. We want to ensure that more women each year are able to access evidence-based specialist mental health care during the perinatal period. This includes access to psychological therapies and specialist community or inpatient care. The importance of this is reflected in both the <a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/wp-content/uploads/2016/02/national-maternity-review-report.pdf" target="_blank">NHS England ‘Better Births</a>’ report of the National Maternity Review (2016) and the ‘Five Year Forward View for Mental Health.’</p><p> </p><p>General practitioners (GPs) and primary care teams have a role in supporting the identification of perinatal mental illness and treatment, and are part of an integrated pathway of services.</p><p> </p><p>The Better Births report outlined that better postnatal care was a key requirement for improved maternity services. It recommended that women should have access to their midwife and obstetrician as they require after having had their baby, as well as the need to ensure a smooth transition to on-going care in the community from their GP and health visitor.</p><p> </p><p>Forty-four Local Maternity Systems have come together across sustainability and transformation partnership footprints to lead the transformation of local maternity services, and are developing plans to deliver the vision of Better Births, including the recommendations on better postnatal care. Additional national support will be provided through an Expert Reference Group, convened by NHS England, to identify further opportunities to support improvements to postnatal care.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894902/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-09T15:40:26.023Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894902/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894902/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-30","Postnatal Depression","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, with reference to the report of the National Childbirth Trust,  The Hidden Half: Bringing postnatal mental illness out of hiding, published in June 2017 and NICE guidance, Postnatal care up to 8 weeks after birth, last updated in February 2015, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that all new mothers are asked about their mental health by a GP at six to eights weeks postnatally.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","139547"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894903","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-03","<p>An Impact Assessment will accompany the proposed changes to law and guidance, following the consultation about how Regulation 1071/2009 applies to the issue and use of section 19 and 22 permits under the Transport Act 1985. The detail of the Assessment is unlikely to cover impacts in each parliamentary constituency.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894903/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T14:35:41.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894903/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894903/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-30","Community Transport: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make an assessment of the effect on community transport services in each parliamentary constituency of the proposals in the Consultation on the use of section 19 and section 22 permits for road passenger transport in Great Britain, published in February 2018.","false","Biography information for Grahame Morris","Easington","Grahame Morris","139461"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894904","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2018-05-03","<p>National statistics on the percentage of children in low income are set out in the annual &quot;Households Below Average Income&quot; publication. Figures on the percentage of children in low income in London can be found in the link below, in table 4.16ts for relative low income, and 4.22ts for absolute low income. These are split into before housing costs (BHC) and after housing costs (AHC). Due to small sample sizes at a regional level, figures are available as three-year rolling averages.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p><a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/692047/children-hbai-timeseries-1994-95-2016-17-tables.ods" target="_blank">https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/692047/children-hbai-timeseries-1994-95-2016-17-tables.ods</a></p>","North West Hampshire","Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894904/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T09:12:49.977Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894904/answer","Biography information for Kit Malthouse","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894904/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2018-04-30","Children: Poverty","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what recent assessment she has made of trends in the level of child poverty in London.","false","Biography information for Vicky Foxcroft","Lewisham, Deptford","Vicky Foxcroft","139548"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894905","Home Office","false","2018-05-03","<p>The Government recognises fully the contribution that doctors working in the NHS – and other professionals – make to the UK.</p><p>Doctors in specialisms which the Migration Advisory Committee have recognised as being in shortage in the UK already receive priority within the Tier 2 allocation system. None of these roles, which include consultants specialising in clinical radiology and emergency medicine, have been refused places. Over a third of all Tier 2 places go to the NHS.</p><p>We continue to monitor the operation of Tier 2 to ensure that it strikes the right balance between supporting employers – including the NHS - accessing talent from overseas and that it works in the national interest and protects the resident labour market.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894905/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T16:00:20.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894905/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894905/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-30","Doctors: Migrant Workers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that doctors from India that have received job offers to work in the NHS are given visas.","false","Biography information for Preet Kaur Gill","Birmingham, Edgbaston","Preet Kaur Gill","139579"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894906","Department for Education","false","2018-05-09","<p>Information on the use of assistive technology in higher education can be found in this 2017 report, commissioned by the then Higher Education Funding Council for England: <a href="http://www.hefce.ac.uk/pubs/rereports/year/2017/modelsofsupport/" target="_blank">http://www.hefce.ac.uk/pubs/rereports/year/2017/modelsofsupport/</a>.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894906/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-09T15:35:34.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894906/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894906/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-04-30","Disabled Students' Allowances","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 24 April 2018 to Question 135864 on Disabled Students' Allowances, what assessment his Department has made of of trends in the level of reliance of disabled students’ on assistive technology.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","139378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894907","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-09","<p>As set out in August 2017 in the UK position paper on Northern Ireland and Ireland, and reiterated in my rt. hon. Friend the Prime Minister’s Mansion House speech, the Government wants the single electricity market to continue to operate across Ireland and Northern Ireland after EU exit. We continue to work across Government and with our EU partners to achieve this aim.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894907/answer",,,,,"139403 ; 139404","2018-05-09T11:47:35.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894907/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894907/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-30","Electricity: Republic of Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union on maintaining the single electricity market with the Republic of Ireland after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","139402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894908","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-09","<p>As set out in August 2017 in the UK position paper on Northern Ireland and Ireland, and reiterated in my rt. hon. Friend the Prime Minister’s Mansion House speech, the Government wants the single electricity market to continue to operate across Ireland and Northern Ireland after EU exit. We continue to work across Government and with our EU partners to achieve this aim.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894908/answer",,,,,"139402 ; 139404","2018-05-09T11:47:35.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894908/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894908/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-30","Electricity: Republic of Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions he has had with the Irish Government on maintaining the single electricity market after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","139403"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894909","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-09","<p>As set out in August 2017 in the UK position paper on Northern Ireland and Ireland, and reiterated in my rt. hon. Friend the Prime Minister’s Mansion House speech, the Government wants the single electricity market to continue to operate across Ireland and Northern Ireland after EU exit. We continue to work across Government and with our EU partners to achieve this aim.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894909/answer",,,,,"139402 ; 139403","2018-05-09T11:47:35.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894909/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894909/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-30","Electricity: Republic of Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions he has had with Cabinet colleagues on maintaining the single electricity market with the Republic of Ireland after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","139404"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894910","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-08","<p>The Government’s priority is to maintain affordable, clean, and secure energy supplies for businesses and households. We share the EU’s ambition to make energy trading easier and more efficient by opening up national markets, and increasing the level of interconnection between them, including between all parts of the UK and Ireland.</p><p> </p><p>My rt. hon. Friend the Prime Minister has said that we want to protect the single electricity market across Ireland and Northern Ireland; and we also want to continue arrangements that allow efficient trade of electricity to take place between the Ireland-Northern Ireland single electricity market and Great Britain. Outcomes relating to the EU Single Market and Customs Union, however, are matters for negotiations, and we are unable to comment on this until negotiations conclude.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894910/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-08T15:59:20.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894910/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894910/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-30","Electricity: Republic of Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what estimate he has made of the potential tariffs that will fall on the UK when importing electricity from the Republic of Ireland in the event that the UK leaves the Single Market and Customs Union.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","139405"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894911","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-09","<p>The Government is committed to making sure consumers have secure, affordable and clean energy now and in the future.</p><p> </p><p>The Capacity Market delivers secure supplies of electricity to homes and businesses and will continue to do so after Brexit. The GB gas market is one of the most liquid and developed markets in the world and provides security through diversity of supply, the majority of which does not depend on a relationship with the EU.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is currently considering all aspects of its future relationship with the EU, including the arrangements for trading energy with the EU. However, energy security remains a priority, not just for the UK but for the whole of Europe, and we will work both domestically and with our trading partners to ensure that we have the energy we need.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894911/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-09T11:47:59.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894911/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894911/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-30","Energy Supply","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what recent assessment he has made of levels of energy (a) security and (b) availability in the UK after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","139406"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894912","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-03","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894912/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T13:10:06.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894912/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894912/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-30","Sexually Transmitted Infections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many cases of neonatal herpes there has been in the last three years; and how many of those cases resulted in a death.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","139592"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894913","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-05-09","<p>The Government’s priority is to maintain affordable, clean, and secure energy supplies for businesses and households. We share the EU’s ambition to make energy trading easier and more efficient by opening up national markets, and increasing the level of interconnection between them, including between all parts of the UK and Ireland.</p><p> </p><p>We want to continue arrangements that allow efficient trade of electricity to take place between the Ireland-Northern Ireland single electricity market and Great Britain, and to closely collaborate on current and future regulatory and technical arrangements. Outcomes relating to the EU Single Market and the Customs Union are matters for negotiations, and we are unable to comment on this until negotiations conclude.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894913/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-09T11:48:21.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894913/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894913/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-04-30","Electricity Interconnectors: Republic of Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment he has made of the effect of the UK leaving the EU single market and Customs Union on the energy interconnector between the UK and Ireland.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","139407"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894914","Department for Exiting the European Union ","false","2018-05-09","<p>At the March European Council the EU adopted guidelines on the framework for the future EU-UK relationship. Discussions on the future relationship are now being taken forward.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>As the Prime Minister set out in her Mansion House speech, while any agreement on our future relationship with the EU must respect the sovereignty of both the UK’s and EU’s legal orders, the UK would like to secure broad energy cooperation with the EU, including exploring options for the UK’s continued participation in the EU’s Internal Energy Market.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894914/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-09T16:47:53.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894914/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894914/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union ","Exiting the European Union ","2018-04-30","Energy: UK Trade with EU","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what recent discussions he has had with the EU on maintaining membership of the EU’s Internal Energy Market after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","139408"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894915","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-05-03","<p>The Digital Economy Act 2010 extended the Public Lending Right (PLR), with effect from 1 July 2014, to include the lending of audio-books and the lending of e-books where such lending takes place from library premises. Section 31 of the Digital Economy Act 2017 (DEA 2017), when commenced, will extend the PLR to include the remote lending of e-books and audiobooks, where such lending takes place away from library premises.</p><p> </p><p>The Department intends to shortly consult with interested parties about amending relevant secondary legislation to ensure that it reflects section 31 of the DEA 2017. The Government intends to lay the necessary statutory instruments commencing section 31 of the DEA 2017 and amending relevant secondary legislation as soon as is practicable, following consideration of the responses to consultation.</p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894915/answer",,,,,"139411","2018-05-03T13:53:34.16Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894915/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894915/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-30","Public Lending Right: Electronic Publishing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, if he will publish the timetable for for introducing Public Lending Right to e-book loans.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","139410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894916","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-03","<p>No assessment has yet been made of the potential merits of designating neonatal herpes as a notifiable disease.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894916/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T13:05:42.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894916/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894916/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-30","Sexually Transmitted Infections","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of designating neonatal herpes as a notifiable disease.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","139593"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894917","Department for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","false","2018-05-03","<p>The Digital Economy Act 2010 extended the Public Lending Right (PLR), with effect from 1 July 2014, to include the lending of audio-books and the lending of e-books where such lending takes place from library premises. Section 31 of the Digital Economy Act 2017 (DEA 2017), when commenced, will extend the PLR to include the remote lending of e-books and audiobooks, where such lending takes place away from library premises.</p><p> </p><p>The Department intends to shortly consult with interested parties about amending relevant secondary legislation to ensure that it reflects section 31 of the DEA 2017. The Government intends to lay the necessary statutory instruments commencing section 31 of the DEA 2017 and amending relevant secondary legislation as soon as is practicable, following consideration of the responses to consultation.</p>","Northampton North","Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894917/answer",,,,,"139410","2018-05-03T13:53:34.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894917/answer","Biography information for Michael Ellis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894917/answer",,,,,"10","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","Digital, Culture, Media and Sport","2018-04-30","Public Lending Right: Electronic Publishing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Digital, Culture, Media and Sport, what his policy is on bringing forward legislative proposals to extend public lending rights to e-book loans.","false","Biography information for Kevin Brennan","Cardiff West","Kevin Brennan","139411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894918","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-03","<p>The Government recognises that the A1(M) is a route of strategic importance.</p><p> </p><p>A smart motorway upgrade between junctions six to eight, which is the busiest section along that route, is in the Road Investment Strategy being delivered by Highways England. The early design work is underway and the current Highways England delivery plan target is for this scheme to start work on site by March 2020. It is expected to have a two to three year construction phase. The completed section will have an additional running lane, providing three traffic lanes in both directions.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894918/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T14:16:09.067Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894918/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894918/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-30","A1 (M): Hertfordshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether his Department has plans to widen the A1M  between Stevenage and Welwyn.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","139448"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894919","Department for Transport","false","2018-05-03","<p>Local authorities already have powers to restrict pavement parking and issue penalty charges to offenders. However, the Department for Transport is currently gathering evidence on the issue of pavement parking, and will be considering the effectiveness of current legislation. We expect to draw conclusions later this year.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894919/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T14:18:43.723Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894919/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894919/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2018-04-30","Parking: Pedestrian Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the potential merits of introducing legislative proposals to issue fines for motorists who park cars on pavements.","false","Biography information for Grant Shapps","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps","139449"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894920","Wales Office","false","2018-05-08","<p>The Government’s priority is to maintain affordable, clean, and secure energy supplies for businesses and households. We share the EU’s ambition to make energy trading easier and more efficient by opening up national markets, and increasing the level of interconnection between them, including between the Republic of Ireland, and all parts of the UK.</p><p> </p><p>We want to continue arrangements that allow efficient trade of electricity to take place between the single electricity market and Great Britain across the East-West interconnector, and to closely collaborate on current and future regulatory and technical arrangements. Outcomes relating to the EU Single Market and the Customs Union are matters for negotiations, and we are unable to comment on this until negotiations conclude.</p>","Vale of Glamorgan","Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894920/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-08T11:49:27.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894920/answer","Biography information for Alun Cairns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894920/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2018-04-30","Electricity Interconnectors: Wales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what discussions he has had with Cabinet colleagues on the effect of the UK leaving the EU Single Market and Customs Union on the East-West Interconnector.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","139409"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894921","Home Office","false","2018-05-09","<p>The Home Office is producing a new, simplified digital system for applications for settled status, the EU Settlement Scheme. Individuals’ status will be recorded electronically and the Home Office will have a long-term record of EU citizens and their family members who are living here with settled status. Those records and relevant Home Office data will be stored securely in accordance with relevant legislation and Home Office data security standards which apply across all data sets within the Home Office. We will provide methods for applicants to view, update and confirm that their data is still on file.</p><p>The Settlement Scheme is still being developed and discussed with stakeholders, and we will be setting out further details in the coming months.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894921/answer",,,,,"137395","2018-05-09T17:02:54.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894921/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894921/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-30","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that EU citizens making immigration or residency applications will be able to confirm that their relevant data and documentation is still on file with his Department after June 2021.","false","Biography information for Sir Vince Cable","Twickenham","Sir Vince Cable","139353"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894922","Home Office","false","2018-05-03","<p>Recruitment is underway to bring existing UKVI European Casework staffing levels to circa 1,500 ahead of the EU Exit Settlement Scheme launch at the end of this year. We are also establishing a new Customer Resolution Centre for the EU Exit Settlement Scheme. This is a brand new ‘in-house’ team who will answer customer enquiries by phone and email seven days a week.</p><p> </p><p>Operational units across the Home Office actively monitor workflows to ensure sufficient resources are in place to meet demand and will continue to do so throughout negotiations and as the UK leaves the EU. Any resultant changes to resource requirements will be factored into strategic planning.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894922/answer",,,,,,"2018-05-03T16:02:29.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894922/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894922/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-04-30","Home Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate he has made of the total number of additional contact staff his Department will employ to answer EU citizens’ immigration and residence queries.","false","Biography information for Sir Vince Cable","Twickenham","Sir Vince Cable","139354"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894923","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-09","<p>NHS England has advised that the Patient Reported Outcome Measure (PROM) on hernia repair did not demonstrate significant improvements in quality of outcomes for many patients and was not implemented very widely.</p><p> </p><p>The Hernia Outcomes Campaign team are in discussion with the Royal College of Surgeons of England, with the British Hernia Society, the Getting It Right First Time team and NHS England about potentially constructing and testing a more useful PROM for hernia outcomes.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England has advised that no specific guidance is issued to clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) regarding the development of commissioning policies for inguinal hernia repair.</p><p> </p><p>It is up to CCGs to decide how services are delivered at a local level and to decide the criteria that they use to determine their commissioning policies for hernia repair. In doing so, they are expected to take account of any National Institute for Health and Care Excellence Quality Standards that are relevant to this.</p><p> </p><p>Individual surgeons have a responsibility for assessing the outcomes of their operations and should make this information available in summary form to prospective patients to help them make effective decisions about whether or not to choose surgical treatment.</p><p> </p><p>A representative of NHS England has met with members of the Hernias Outcomes Campaign and discussed the contents of their 2017 report. NHS England concur that for patients with few symptoms an effective process of shared decision-making between patient and surgeon may well result in a choice not to opt for immediate surgery.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894923/answer",,,,,"139585 ; 139586 ; 139587 ; 139588 ; 139589","2018-05-09T11:16:58.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894923/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894923/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-30","Hernias: Surgical Mesh Implants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment has his Department made of the effect of removing the Patient Reported Outcome Measure on hernia repair on the commissioning policies used by Clinical Commissioning Groups.","false","Biography information for Eleanor Smith","Wolverhampton South West","Eleanor Smith","139583"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894924","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-05-09","<p>A table containing the number of inguinal hernia repair procedures undertaken by the National Health Service in England by clinical commissioning group of treatment for the years 2012/13 to 2016/17 is attached.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894924/answer","PQ139584 data.xlsx","PQ139584 data.xlsx","PQ139584 attached data","PQ139584 attached data",,"2018-05-09T11:21:58.443Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894924/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/894924/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-04-30","Hernias: Surgical Mesh Implants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care,  how many inguinal hernia repair procedures has NHS undertaken in each Clinical Commissioning Group in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Eleanor Smith","Wolverhampton South West","Eleanor Smith","139584"
